methods.name: boolean writeData(RowSetInternal caller) throws SQLException
methods.comment: * Writes the changes in this RowSetWriter object's * rowset back to the data source from which it got its data. * * @param caller the RowSet object (1) that has implemented the * RowSetInternal interface, (2) with which this writer is * registered, and (3) that called this method internally * @return true if the modified data was written; false * if not, which will be the case if there is a conflict * @exception SQLException if a database access error occurs
